div.span: React 17 replaced ReactDom.render() with the createRoot function.
CreateRoot() creates a new root container and returns a reference to it for later rendering components,
as contrast to ReactDOM.render() which renders components directly to a specific DOM node.

div.span: Using crate-react-app instead of React CDN:
NavLink is a react-router-dom component to browse through a React application and
add extra styling attributes to the element,
but using an anchor tag for navigation will force a page reload and
cause all the components to be rendered again.
Also styling an active link differently is easier with NavLink instead of Link component.
